    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In pure Python mode, when a Python class with 0-1 known base classes defines a constant `__slots__` attribute, it makes sense to compile it into an extension class automatically, and make the defined slots `object` attributes.\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/433\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Can be implemented as part of the `AlignFunctionDefinitions` transform, which essentially does the same thing for Python class type overrides found in `.pxd` files.",
